### APIM Subscription Manager — API Test Requests
### Use with JetBrains HTTP Client, VS Code REST Client, or similar
### Base URL is configured via http-client.env.json

### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### Subscriptions (User)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────

### List subscriptions for current user
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/subscriptions
X-User-Id: user-alice
Accept: application/json

### List subscriptions with filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/subscriptions?name=prod&sortBy=createdAt&desc=true&page=1&pageSize=10
X-User-Id: user-alice
Accept: application/json

### Create a new subscription
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/subscriptions
X-User-Id: user-alice
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "displayName": "My Test Subscription",
  "productIds": ["product-analytics", "product-weather"]
}

### Get subscription by ID
### Replace {id} with an actual subscription ID from the create response
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/subscriptions/{id}
X-User-Id: user-alice
Accept: application/json

### Rotate subscription keys
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/subscriptions/{id}/rotate
X-User-Id: user-alice

### Update subscription products
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/subscriptions/{id}/products
X-User-Id: user-alice
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productIds": ["product-analytics", "product-maps", "product-search"]
}

### Cancel subscription
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/subscriptions/{id}
X-User-Id: user-alice

### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### Admin
### ─────────────────────────────────────────

### List all subscriptions (admin view)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/subscriptions
Accept: application/json

### List all with filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/subscriptions?owner=user-alice&state=Active&sortBy=displayName&desc=false&page=1&pageSize=10
Accept: application/json

### Get rotation status (subscriptions due or approaching rotation)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/subscriptions/rotation-status
Accept: application/json
